                        <h1>Evidence-Based Management</h1>
                        <div id="main-content" class="wiki-content group">
                            <p>An empirical approach that helps organizations to continuously improve customer outcomes,
                                organizational capabilities and business results under conditions of uncertainty.</p>
                            <p>By using experimentation and evidence we can help our teams improve performance and refine
                                our goals.</p>

                            <ul>
                                <li>Strategic Goals - An aspirational goal that represents something important the
                                    organization would like to achieve. Results in improved happiness, safety, security,
                                    or well-being
                                    of the recipients of some product or service</li>
                                <li>Intermediate Goals - achievements that indicate that we are on our way to the
                                    strategic goal</li>
                                <li>Immediate Tactical Goals - critical near-term objectives that allow us to work
                                    towards the Intermediate Goals</li>
                                <li>Starting State - where the organization is relative to the Strategic Goal at the
                                    start of the Journey</li>
                                <li>Current State - where the organization is relative to the Strategic Goal at the
                                    present time.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <img src="../../images/ebm.png">

                            <h2>Key Value Areas (KVAs)</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Unrealized Value - the satisfaction gap between a beneficiary's desired outcome and
                                    their current experience</li>
                                <li>Current Value - current state in realizing the desired outcomes</li>
                                <li>Time-to-Market - responsiveness in delivering value</li>
                                <li>Ability-to-Innovate - effectiveness in delivering value</li>
                            </ul>
